# Luma Project Overview

Luma is a TypeScript CLI tool for zero-downtime Docker deployments to your own servers. It provides blue-green deployments, automatic SSL certificates, health checks, and multi-server support.

## Project Structure

- **Entry Point**: [src/index.ts](mdc:src/index.ts) - Main CLI entry point with command routing
- **Commands**: [src/commands/](mdc:src/commands) - All CLI commands implementation
- **Core Functionality**:
  - [src/commands/deploy.ts](mdc:src/commands/deploy.ts) - Main deployment logic
  - [src/commands/blue-green.ts](mdc:src/commands/blue-green.ts) - Zero-downtime deployment strategy
  - [src/commands/setup.ts](mdc:src/commands/setup.ts) - Server setup and configuration
  - [src/commands/init.ts](mdc:src/commands/init.ts) - Project initialization
  - [src/commands/status.ts](mdc:src/commands/status.ts) - Deployment status checking

## Key Technologies

- **Runtime**: Bun/Node.js 18+
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Dependencies**: ssh2-promise, js-yaml, zod
- **Target**: Ubuntu/Debian servers with Docker

## Configuration Files

- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Project metadata and dependencies
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration
- `luma.yml` - User deployment configuration (created by init command)
- `.luma/secrets` - Secure credentials storage

## Build & Release

- Build target: `dist/` directory
- CLI binary: `dist/index.js`
- Package: `@elitan/luma` on npm
